{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"33c52491-67b7-446a-ba6b-fc09679acafd","content":"Yes, you'll hit **framework compatibility issues**. MSTest v3 dropped support for end-of-life TFMs. Two of your three targets are affected:\n\n| Target | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped (EOL) |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped (EOL) |\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for .NET (Core) targets. You'd need to update those to at least `net6.0`.\n\n**Other migration notes:**\n- MSTest v3 consolidates `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` into a single **`MSTest`** package (or the `MSTest.Sdk`).\n- There are behavioral breaking changes (e.g., `TestContext` must be non-nullable, some removed/changed APIs, default class-cleanup lifecycle changes).\n\n**To migrate**, you'd update your TFMs and packages, e.g.:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net6.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n...\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.x.x\" />\n```\n\nWould you like me to apply the migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fa4d5160-4dbc-48b0-8a9d-15ef5dd99796","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nMSTest v3 has some important compatibility changes:\n\n1. **Dropped framework support**: MSTest v3 dropped support for older target frameworks. Specifically:\n   - `.NET 5.0` is no longer supported (it's end-of-life). MSTest v3 requires at minimum `.NET 6.0` for .NET targets.\n   - `netcoreapp3.1` is no longer supported (end-of-life). \n   - `.NET Framework 4.6.2` (`net462`) remains supported and meets the minimum requirement.\n\nSo the migration would require updating `net5.0` to `net6.0` or later, and `netcoreapp3.1` would need to be dropped or updated, while `net462` can stay as-is.\n\nBeyond the TFM compatibility issue, MSTest v3 also consolidates the individual packages into a single `MSTest` meta-package and introduces breaking changes like requiring non-nullable `TestContext` properties and altering class cleanup lifecycle behavior, though the TFM incompatibility is the immediate blocker for this user.","outputTokens":794,"requestId":"083A:16A6CA:8406C7B:92FEF4A:69EAD524"},"id":"188c5d72-9035-417a-8c7b-b40504f9621d","timestamp":"2026-04-24T02:28:05.246Z","parentId":"e22913cc-3b49-4965-b5e5-a4c7b8310015"}
